17/03/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- As chair of the South-East European Co-operation Process (SEECP), Athens is hosting a two-day conference of member countries' parliament speakers. The event, which began on Friday (17 March), will focus on regional collaboration, democratisation, civil society and the role of SEECP. Representatives of the parliamentary assemblies of the Council of Europe, the European Parliament, NATO, the OSCE and the Black Sea Economic Co-operation pact are also attending.
In other news, the interior ministry representatives of SEE states will meet on Saturday at a Bulgarian resort. Security and regional co-operation will be the focus of talks. (Greek Parliament Web site, Albanian News - 17/03/06; BNR - 16/03/06)
